<h2 id="unrenderable-document-error"><a class="toclink" href="#unrenderable-document-error">Unrenderable document error</a></h2>
<p>It is common to see the following error on Asterisk:</p>
<p>[2012-06-14 12:08:46] ERROR Adhearsion::Call: 008410de-feb6-48a6-9390-2388a89412ef: Error playing back the prompt: Output failed for argument "5" due to #<Punchblock::ProtocolError: name="unrenderable document error" text="The provided document could not be rendered." call_id=nil component_id=nil></p>
<p>What this means is that the requested output document could not be rendered on the call, and ocurrs most commonly when using Asterisk or FreeSWITCH without a text to speach engine, but attempting to use the speak/say CallController methods. In this case, Asterisk cannot invoke text-to-speech and so raises this error.</p>
<p>Many people see this error when calling into a default generated Adhearsion application on Asterisk, and this is because the SimonGame uses text-to-speech.</p>
