<h2 id="stack-exhaustion"><a class="toclink" href="#stack-exhaustion">Stack exhaustion</a></h2>
<p>A stack error is sometimes encountered when running on Ruby 1.9.3 via RVM, looking similar to the following:</p>
<p>[2012-11-15 21:32:45] ERROR Celluloid: Punchblock::Translator::Freeswitch crashed!
SystemStackError: stack level too deep</p>
<p>It is a known issue with Celluloid and RVM, and the best solution is to uninstall your current Ruby, update RVM using "rvm get head" and reinstall Ruby.</p>
<p>rbenv does not exhibit this issue.</p>
